{
  "info": {
    "name": "ClientSide Ecommerce API",
    "description": "Storefront API: health, auth (register/login), Google OAuth2, JWT exchange, profile, service area, catalog list + search.\n\n**Setup**\n- Run `npm run dev` (default port **4100**). Create **`.env`** per **README**; set `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `API_PUBLIC_URL`, Google vars for OAuth.\n- `npm run db:migrate`. A **shop** row must exist; set collection variable **`shopId`** to its UUID.\n\n**JWT**\n- Response includes `accessToken`. Payload: `role`, `customerId`; `shopId` may be present when the user has exactly one active shop (register or single-shop login).\n- Authenticated routes: `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`.\n\n**Google sign-in (browser)**\n- Redirect URI in Google Cloud Console: `{API_PUBLIC_URL}/api/oauth/callback/google`.\n- After Google, the API redirects to **`GET /api/oauth/success`** (or your `callbackURL`) and sets cookie **`storefront_oauth_exchange`**. Then `POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt` with **`credentials: 'include'`** (same origin as the API). **`POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social`** (not GET).\n- Email-only body `{ \"email\" }` only if `ALLOW_EMAIL_ONLY_JWT_EXCHANGE=true` (non-production).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4100" },
    { "key": "shopId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "buyer@example.com" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "secret12" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
            "description": "Returns `status` and `service`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "  if (j.shop && j.shop.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('shopId', j.shop.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"shopId\": \"{{shopId}}\",\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Test Buyer\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register",
            "description": "**201** — `accessToken`, `user`, `shop`, `customer`, `profile`, `role: customer`.\n\n**409** — cannot complete registration for this shop (e.g. active membership conflict).\n\nTest script saves `accessToken` and `shopId` on success."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "  if (j.shopIds && j.shopIds[0]) pm.collectionVariables.set('shopId', j.shopIds[0]);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
            "description": "**200** — `accessToken`, `shopIds`, `profile` (per shop). **401** — invalid credentials.\n\nTest script saves `accessToken` and first `shopId` when present."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/oauth/jwt",
            "description": "**Preferred:** send the **`storefront_oauth_exchange`** httpOnly cookie set after `GET /api/oauth/callback/google` (browser + `credentials: 'include'` from the API origin).\n\n**Dev-only:** JSON `{ \"email\" }` works only if `ALLOW_EMAIL_ONLY_JWT_EXCHANGE=true` (forbidden in production). **403** when disabled and no valid cookie.\n\n**200** — same shape as login; saves `accessToken` in test script."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me/profile",
            "description": "**401** without valid Bearer token."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH /api/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"displayName\": \"Updated Name\",\n  \"address\": {\n    \"city\": \"London\",\n    \"postalCode\": \"SW1A 1AA\",\n    \"line1\": \"10 Example Street\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me/profile",
            "description": "Partial update. Do not send `address: {}` (validation error). `lat`/`lng` must both be set or both null."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "OAuth (Google)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/oauth/ok",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/oauth/ok",
            "description": "Liveness: `{ \"ok\": true }`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/oauth/dev/google-start",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/oauth/dev/google-start?shopId={{shopId}}",
            "description": "Redirect to Google (use a real browser). Optional `callbackURL` (e.g. storefront). Requires `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` / `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Origin", "value": "http://localhost:5173" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"provider\": \"google\",\n  \"disableRedirect\": true,\n  \"callbackURL\": \"http://localhost:4100/\",\n  \"additionalData\": {\n    \"shopId\": \"{{shopId}}\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/oauth/sign-in/social",
            "description": "**`disableRedirect: true`** — JSON `{ \"url\" }` for Postman. Browser flow: omit it; use `credentials: 'include'` and do not paste the returned URL into a new tab (state cookie).\n\n**`additionalData.shopId`** optional: provision membership for that shop after Google verifies email.\n\n**503** if Google OAuth env is not configured."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Shops",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/shops/:shopId/service-area/check",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"lat\": 12.9716,\n  \"lng\": 77.5946\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/shops/{{shopId}}/service-area/check",
            "description": "Response: `inServiceArea`, `distanceM`, `maxRadiusM`, `code`, `message`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Catalog",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/search",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/search?shopId={{shopId}}&type=both&q=&categoryId=&parentId=&availability=&productSort=name&productOrder=asc&categorySort=sort_order&categoryOrder=asc&productLimit=100&productOffset=0&categoryLimit=500&categoryOffset=0",
            "description": "Search/filter/sort products and/or categories in one call.\n\n**shopId** or **x-shop-id** header required.\n\n**type:** `products` | `categories` | `both` (default both).\n\n**q:** optional text (matches product/category **name** and **slug**).\n\n**Products:** `categoryId`, `availability` (`in_stock` | `out_of_stock` | `unknown`), `productSort` (`name` | `price` | `created_at` | `availability`), `productOrder` (`asc` | `desc`), `productLimit` (1–100), `productOffset`.\n\n**Categories:** `parentId` (omit/null = root only; UUID = children), `categorySort` (`sort_order` | `name` | `created_at`), `categoryOrder`, `categoryLimit` (1–500), `categoryOffset`.\n\n**200:** `{ \"products\": [...], \"categories\": [...] }` (empty arrays for sides not requested)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/items (query shopId)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/items?shopId={{shopId}}",
            "description": "Active products (alias of **GET /api/catalog/products** without category filter)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/items (header x-shop-id)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/items",
            "description": "Same as query `shopId`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/categories (root)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/categories?shopId={{shopId}}",
            "description": "Root active categories. Optional `parentId=<uuid>` for children."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/products",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/products?shopId={{shopId}}",
            "description": "Active products. Optional `categoryId`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
